survived.Column Description: Indicates whether the passenger survived (1) or died (0).

age.Column Description: Age of the passenger in years.

sibsp.Column Description: Number of siblings/spouses aboard the Titanic.

parch.Column Description: Number of parents/children aboard the Titanic.

embarked.Column Description: Port of embarkation: C = Cherbourg, Q = Queenstown, S = Southampton.

class.Column Description: Travel class as a categorical feature.

adult_male.Column Description: Boolean indicating if the passenger is an adult male.

deck.Column Description: Deck location of the passenger's cabin.

alive.Column Description: Indicates whether the passenger survived ('yes') or died ('no').

alone.Column Description: Boolean indicating if the passenger traveled alone.

Dataset Insights.Overall Trends: To be analyzed based on specific time-series data, if available.
Dataset Insights.Clusters or Groups: Clustering analysis can be applied, but is dataset-dependent.
